        question: "An NP evaluating a child for ADHD finds symptoms only at school with no symptoms at home. The appropriate next step is:",
        options: ["Diagnose ADHD predominantly inattentive type based on school symptoms alone","Explore whether the school environment is contributing to symptoms and consider alternative diagnoses","Start a stimulant trial to see if school performance improves","Refer directly to psychiatry without further evaluation"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "DSM-5 criterion C requires symptoms present in 2 or more settings. Symptoms isolated to one setting suggest a situational cause (learning disability, anxiety, classroom environment mismatch, bullying) rather than ADHD. The NP should explore alternative explanations and obtain collateral information from parents before diagnosing."
