        rationale: "Bipolar disorder must be screened for before starting stimulants. Stimulant medications can trigger or exacerbate manic episodes in patients with undiagnosed bipolar disorder. If bipolar disorder is suspected, mood stabilization should be established before considering ADHD treatment. Screening for mood episodes, family history of bipolar disorder, and mood cycling is essential."
