        correct: 1,
        rationale: "In primary adrenal insufficiency, the destroyed adrenal cortex cannot produce cortisol, so the pituitary increases ACTH production through loss of negative feedback. ACTH shares a precursor molecule (POMC) with melanocyte-stimulating hormone, causing increased melanin production and hyperpigmentation of skin creases, scars, and mucous membranes."
